  "paragraphs": [
    {
      "para_id": "Q009691.1",
      "line_range": "1",
      "translation": "(i 1) By his firm command , Enlil , the king of all lands , the father of all gods .... ... ( Uš ) removed the stela and repositioned it towards the plain of Lagaš ."
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q009691.10",
      "line_range": "10",
      "translation": "(i 22) By ( Enlil’s ) just command , Ninĝirsu , Enlil’s warrior , did battle with Umma . By Enlil’s command , he cast on it the great battle-net , and heaped up a burial mound for it on the plain ."
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q009691.21",
      "line_range": "21",
      "translation": "(ii 1') The leader of Umma took ... as interest bearing loan . It yielded interest and accummulated to 144,000 guru. As this ( amount ) of barley could not be repaid , Ur-Luma , ruler of Umma , washed away Ninĝirsu’s and Nanše’s boundary dyke . He set fire to their stelae and tore each of them out ."
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q009691.37",
      "line_range": "37",
      "translation": "(iii 5) Il claimed the rulership of Umma for himself . ...."
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q009691.42",
      "line_range": "42",
      "translation": "(iii 1') ... ( En-metena ) built the substructure of the Namnunda-kiĝara of stone . He constructed its dyke from the Tigris to the Id-nun . For Ninĝirsu , his master who loves him , and for Nanše , the lady who loves him , he restored it ."
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q009691.53",
      "line_range": "53",
      "translation": "(iii 12') May En-metena's personal god , Šul-MUŠxPA , intercede forever for En-metena’s well-being with Ninĝirsu and Nanše !"
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q009691.62",
      "line_range": "62",
      "translation": "(iv 21) ... Having cast on him his great battle-net , may Ninĝirsu pound him down with his majestic hands , tread on him with his majestic feet !"
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q009691.66",
      "line_range": "66",
      "translation": "(iv 25) Having revolted against him in his city , may the people kill him in the middle of his city !"
    }
  ],
